This task involves a multi-step process to address the underlying research or evaluation question of your eventual survey. Please follow the directions below[^1]

1.  First download the following

<center>
<a onclick="fetch(&#39;data:application/zip;base64,&#39;).then(res =&gt; res.blob()).then(blob =&gt; {&#10;      const downloadURL = window.URL.createObjectURL(blob);&#10;      const a = document.createElement(&#39;a&#39;);&#10;      document.body.appendChild(a);&#10;      a.href = downloadURL;&#10;      a.download = &#39;Survey Skeleton.zip&#39;; a.click();&#10;      window.URL.revokeObjectURL(downloadURL);&#10;      document.body.removeChild(a);&#10;    });">
<button class="btn btn-primary hvr-sweep-to-left"><i class="fa fa-save"></i> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style='color:#ffffff'>Download</span></button>
</a>
</center>

<br>

2.  Open both files and review the variable names and descriptions in the codebook

3.  Fill out the following columns[^2]

- **Item**. Survey items in the order they will currently appear

- **ItemType**. Question type as allowed by [Qualtrics](https://www.qualtrics.com/support/survey-platform/survey-module/editing-questions/question-types-guide/question-types-overview/)

- **Measure**. Direct measure of the item

- **Latent**. Indirect measure of a category

4.  After you have completed the draft, login to the [WVU Qualtrics](https://wvu.qualtrics.com) page, create a new survey, and construct an instrument that is a direct reflection of the skeleton

5.  Share your survey by enabling [Collaboration](https://www.qualtrics.com/support/survey-platform/my-projects/sharing-a-project/)[^3]

6.  Fill out the **Index** column with the item number provided in Qualtrics. Consider [auto-numbering](https://www.qualtrics.com/support/survey-platform/survey-module/survey-tools/auto-number-questions/) your questions to renumber them in order

7.  Rename the document by following the [submission guidelines](/tasks/#submission-formatting), save it in `xlsx` format, and submit this document to <a target="_blank" href="https://ecampus.wvu.edu/">eCampus</a><br><br>

<center>
<p id="rounded_corners">
All incremental deliverables can be found on the main <a href="/tasks/#deliverables">Tasks</a> page
<p>
</center>

<br />

[^1]: These items assume that Qualtrics is used. If you are using another mode, please amend your responses to for the requirements of that platform

[^2]: While not required at the current time, you are free to fill out any of the remaining columns as needed

[^3]: Please disallow editing privileges
